anguage/configure','default','None.','6.11'),(968,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/configure','default','Path prefix only.','6.11'),(969,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/configure','default','Path prefix with language fallback.','6.11'),(970,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/configure','default','Domain name only.','6.11'),(971,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/configure','default','Select the mechanism used to determine your site\'s presentation language. <strong>Modifying this setting may break all incoming URLs and should be used with caution in a production environment.</strong>','6.11'),(972,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/configure','default','Save settings','6.11'),(973,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/configure','default','Language negotiation settings determine the site\'s presentation language. Available options include:','6.11'),(974,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/configure','default','<strong>None.</strong> The default language is used for site presentation, though users may (optionally) select a preferred language on the <em>My Account</em> page. (User language preferences will be used for site e-mails, if available.)','6.11'),(975,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/configure','default','<strong>Path prefix only.</strong> The presentation language is determined by examining the path for a language code or other custom string that matches the path prefix (if any) specified for each language. If a suitable prefix is not identified, the default language is used. <em>Example: \"example.com/de/contact\" sets presentation language to German based on the use of \"de\" within the path.</em>','6.11'),(976,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/configure','default','<strong>Path prefix with language fallback.</strong> The presentation language is determined by examining the path for a language code or other custom string that matches the path prefix (if any) specified for each language. If a suitable prefix is not identified, the display language is determined by the user\'s language preferences from the <em>My Account</em> page, or by the browser\'s language settings. If a presentation language cannot be determined, the default language is used.','6.11'),(977,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/configure','default','<strong>Domain name only.</strong> The presentation language is determined by examining the domain used to access the site, and comparing it to the language domain (if any) specified for each language. If a match is not identified, the default language is used. <em>Example: \"http://de.example.com/contact\" sets presentation language to German based on the use of \"http://de.example.com\" in the domain.</em>','6.11'),(978,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/configure','default','The path prefix or domain name for a language may be set by editing the <a href=\"@languages\">available languages</a>. In the absence of an appropriate match, the site is displayed in the <a href=\"@languages\">default language</a>.','6.11'),(979,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/configure','default','Language negotiation configuration saved.','6.11'),(980,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/edit/es','default','Edit language','6.11'),(981,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/edit/es','default','Language code','6.11'),(982,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/edit/es','default','Language name in English','6.11'),(983,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/edit/es','default','Name of the language in English. Will be available for translation in all languages.','6.11'),(984,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/edit/es','default','Native language name','6.11'),(985,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/edit/es','default','Name of the language in the language being added.','6.11'),(986,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/edit/es','default','Path prefix','6.11'),(987,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/edit/es','default','Language code or other custom string for pattern matching within the path. With language negotiation set to <em>Path prefix only</em> or <em>Path prefix with language fallback</em>, this site is presented in this language when the Path prefix value matches an element in the path. For the default language, this value may be left blank. <strong>Modifying this value will break existing URLs and should be used with caution in a production environment.</strong> <em>Example: Specifying \"deutsch\" as the path prefix for German results in URLs in the form \"www.example.com/deutsch/node\".</em>','6.11'),(988,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/edit/es','default','Language domain','6.11'),(989,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/edit/es','default','Language-specific URL, with protocol. With language negotiation set to <em>Domain name only</em>, the site is presented in this language when the URL accessing the site references this domain. For the default language, this value may be left blank. <strong>This value must include a protocol as part of the string.</strong> <em>Example: Specifying \"http://example.de\" or \"http://de.example.com\" as language domains for German results in URLs in the forms \"http://example.de/node\" and \"http://de.example.com/node\", respectively.</em>','6.11'),(990,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/edit/es','default','Direction that text in this language is presented.','6.11'),(991,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/edit/es','default','Right to left','6.11'),(992,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/language/edit/es','default','Save language','6.11'),(1013,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','There are @count items left to index.','6.12'),(1014,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','%percentage of the site has been indexed.','6.12'),(1015,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','Indexing status','6.12'),(1016,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','Re-index site','6.12'),(1017,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','Indexing throttle','6.12'),(1018,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','Number of items to index per cron run','6.12'),(1019,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','The maximum number of items indexed in each pass of a <a href=\"@cron\">cron maintenance task</a>. If necessary, reduce the number of items to prevent timeouts and memory errors while indexing.','6.12'),(1020,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','Indexing settings','6.12'),(1021,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','<p><em>Changing the settings below will cause the site index to be rebuilt. The search index is not cleared but systematically updated to reflect the new settings. Searching will continue to work but new content won\'t be indexed until all existing content has been re-indexed.</em></p><p><em>The default settings should be appropriate for the majority of sites.</em></p>','6.12'),(1022,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','Minimum word length to index','6.12'),(1023,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','The number of characters a word has to be to be indexed. A lower setting means better search result ranking, but also a larger database. Each search query must contain at least one keyword that is this size (or longer).','6.12'),(1024,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','Simple CJK handling','6.12'),(1025,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','Whether to apply a simple Chinese/Japanese/Korean tokenizer based on overlapping sequences. Turn this off if you want to use an external preprocessor for this instead. Does not affect other languages.','6.12'),(1026,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','Content ranking','6.12'),(1027,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','The following numbers control which properties the content search should favor when ordering the results. Higher numbers mean more influence, zero means the property is ignored. Changing these numbers does not require the search index to be rebuilt. Changes take effect immediately.','6.12'),(1028,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','Keyword relevance','6.12'),(1029,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','Recently posted','6.12'),(1030,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','Number of comments','6.12'),(1031,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','Factor','6.12'),(1032,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','The search engine maintains an index of words found in your site\'s content. To build and maintain this index, a correctly configured <a href=\"@cron\">cron maintenance task</a> is required. Indexing behavior can be adjusted using the settings below.','6.12'),(1033,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','The search module adds the ability to search for content by keywords. Search is often the only practical way to find content on a large site, and is useful for finding both users and posts.','6.12'),(1034,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','To provide keyword searching, the search engine maintains an index of words found in your site\'s content. To build and maintain this index, a correctly configured <a href=\"@cron\">cron maintenance task</a> is required. Indexing behavior can be adjusted using the <a href=\"@searchsettings\">search settings page</a>; for example, the <em>Number of items to index per cron run</em> sets the maximum number of items indexed in each pass of a <a href=\"@cron\">cron maintenance task</a>. If necessary, reduce this number to prevent timeouts and memory errors when indexing.','6.12'),(1035,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search','default','For more information, see the online handbook entry for <a href=\"@search\">Search module</a>.','6.12'),(1036,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search/wipe','default','Are you sure you want to re-index the site?','6.12'),(1037,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search/wipe','default',' The search index is not cleared but systematically updated to reflect the new settings. Searching will continue to work but new content won\'t be indexed until all existing content has been re-indexed. This action cannot be undone.','6.12'),(1038,' img_assist.module:548;950','default','Cancel','6.14'),(1039,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/search/wipe','default','The index will be rebuilt.','6.12'),(1040,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/site-maintenance','default','Site status','6.12'),(1041,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/site-maintenance','default','Online','6.12'),(1042,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/site-maintenance','default','Off-line','6.12'),(1043,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/site-maintenance','default','When set to \"Online\", all visitors will be able to browse your site normally. When set to \"Off-line\", only users with the \"administer site configuration\" permission will be able to access your site to perform maintenance; all other visitors will see the site off-line message configured below. Authorized users can log in during \"Off-line\" mode directly via the <a href=\"@user-login\">user login</a> page.','6.12'),(1044,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/site-maintenance','default','Site off-line message','6.12'),(1045,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/site-maintenance','default','@site is currently under maintenance. We should be back shortly. Thank you for your patience.','6.14'),(1046,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/site-maintenance','default','Message to show visitors when the site is in off-line mode.','6.12'),(1047,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/site-information','default','The name of this website.','6.14'),(1048,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/site-information','default','E-mail address','6.14'),(1049,'/drupal-6.11/?q=es/admin/settings/site-information','default','The <em>From</